hem as being difficulties. I mean, it was the kind of family where people said what they thought, and the central argument that was going on \endash  there were always arguments going on, but the arguments weren\rquote 
t just between my mother and my nurse.  From time to time there were maids, as well, for a period \'85
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid5975301 Ray:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid15155764\charrsid8024348 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
