m not sure I can remember the answer!  (LAUGHS)  It might well have been my mother-in-law, my then mother-in-law, who suggested it, actually, because it\rquote s quite a popular place \endash  or it was \endash 
 for Welsh people to go on holiday in Glyncereiog.  I mean, people tend to go on holiday to the North Wales coast, but if they didn\rquote t want a seaside holiday, they would go to one of these hill villages.  They\rquote re very
 pleasant places to live.  They\rquote re very friendly, even to people who can\rquote t speak Welsh.  And also, there\rquote s lots of fresh food, nice country walks and so on.
