\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid5975301 Ray:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid15155764\charrsid8024348 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid15155764\charrsid8024348 Well, the tension.  You\rquote re coming in as an outsider, you\rquote re trying not to disrupt, but you\rquote re trying to reveal the conflicts that the local people don\rquote 
t want to reveal, or pretend that they are a cosy community. There\rquote s this ideology that we\rquote re all familiar with.  You say, \'93in order to understand how this thing works, we\rquote 
ve got to get a crisis, or something that will show where the lines of division really are\'94. But then, of course, they re-group together and come back.  And after a bit \'85
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid5975301 Ray:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid15155764\charrsid8024348 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid15155764\charrsid8024348 I was saying that there\rquote s you coming in as an outsider, attempting 
to reveal something of reality through exposing conflicts, and the villagers, in a sense, defending what you might call their illusion of \'93community\'94
.  If you succeed, as you did, to reveal some of these conflicts, they would then regroup, eventually, to re-assert their own value system. 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid5975301 Ronald:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid15155764\charrsid8024348 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 
