s very difficult to learn how to behave so that you don\rquote t stick out like a sore thumb in a pub with a group of men who drink together every evening, and have done for the past 20 years!  There\rquote 
s just nowhere where you can slide into the background, and it\rquote s also a place where status is so related to obeying the rules that breaches are very noticeable, whereas if you are sitting in someone\rquote 
s front parlour, and you do something that if one of them did would be considered a terrible solecism, they don\rquote t really notice, because they don\rquote t expect you to know how to behave there.  But it\rquote 
s public, public places, I think, much more \'85
