s written a history of this, but, in fact, there are a lot of general practitioners who, although they\rquote re general practitioners, have played an enormous part in shaping modern medicines, and quite often are mu
ch more noticeable for what [they do] than what the great names do, because sometimes the great names are so remote that they don\rquote t have much real influence.  Their houseman has a lot of influence, but they don\rquote 
t!  (LAUGHS)  So we met the Faulkners and stayed with them, again, through the Communist Party, through the Italian Communist Party. And we lived with them for a while when we first went to Italy, in a house called \'93La Galera\'94
, because it was just Italian for \'93prison\'94 \endash  it was an old prison fort, where rebels were imprisoned \endash  round, with stone walls, and crenellated. 
