\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid15155764\charrsid8024348 
I mean, Gluckman was fairly Left-wing, but by no means Communist, and there was just a general interest in how people managed, and in what sort of ways they might manage better, what one could do to help them. So tha
t all the senior staff of the University \endash  and there were quite a few apart from Gluckman and Devons \endash  who spent their summers in North Wales, would sort of give a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
\i\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid15155764\charrsid8024348 quid pro quo}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid15155764\charrsid8024348 
 by helping people to manoeuvre their way through the school system, what sort o
f subjects they ought to do at the Grammar School in Oswestry, in order to be most likely to be able to follow the courses in a university, which would help in the subjects they wanted to do \endash 
 whether it was agriculture or some other subject which wasn\rquote t so useful, but which would get them Brownie points in getting into a local Grammar School, or going to the Grammar School over the border in Oswestry.
